 the common pool of `ForkJoinPool`. This brings up an interesting question: does loading the factory class then trigger the loading of the `ForkJoinPool` interface? I need to clarify these dependencies to understand any potential issues better.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating classpath configurations**\\n\\nI'm looking into using detached configuration with version 2.11 while including files in the classpath. It seems that Javac would have access to both versions—2.13 through testCompileClasspath and 2.11 directly. Javac will search both versions, and I noted a specific package class is missing in 2.13 but exists in 2.11, so it should be able to locate what I need. Let's see if this setup works as expected!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering configuration changes**\\n\\nI need to modify the support constants and change Scala to avoid using classOf. It seems I should also configure the compileTestJava classpath. However, I wonder if there might still be a conflict with compiling Java. I'll keep that in mind while editing. Additionally, I need to consider the test runtime since native image compilation requires both the necessary Java classes and the 2.11 library.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_yJEFKK5THX4VC90nsprnwpKO|fc_042447f617a89c220169f90d46865c81a0b06907f89061824a", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/src/test/java/org_scala_lang/scala_library/ForkJoinPoolTestSupport.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    public static final String THREAD_FACTORY_PROPERTY = \"java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinPool.common.threadFactory\";\n    public static final String EXCEPTION_HANDLER_PROPERTY = \"java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinPool.common.exceptionHandler\";\n", "newText": "    public static final String THREAD_FACTORY_PROPERTY = \"java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinPool.common.threadFactory\";\n    public static final String EXCEPTION_HANDLER_PROPERTY = \"java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinPool.co